# QA Testing

## Purpose and boundaries

**In scope:** Derive QA artifacts from the current branch diff (`master...HEAD`). Six modes, same discovery base, different output format and depth.

**Out of scope:** Running tests, writing unit tests, implementing code, filing Jira tickets.

**Success:** The dev receives ready-to-use QA artifacts derived from the actual diff — no invented endpoints, no padding, field names verbatim from source.

---

## Disambiguation — when no mode given

Render this decision tree, then the table, then ask "Which one do you want?". **Do not run discovery yet.**

```
Quick chat review              → QA-scenarios
Repo-level QA docs             → QA-notes
Hand-off to another dev        → QA-guide
Importable Postman collection  → QA-postman
Other tooling (curl/.http/…)   → QA-requests
PR description body            → QA-description
```

| Mode | Output | When to use |
|---|---|---|
| `QA-scenarios` | Numbered list in chat | See scenarios without a file |
| `QA-notes` | `.md` with explanations + evidence slots | QA docs that live in the repo |
| `QA-guide` | `.md` vital-only checklist (5–7 items) | Hand-off so another dev runs QA quickly |
| `QA-postman` | `.postman_collection.json` with `pm.test` | You have Postman and want an importable collection |
| `QA-requests` | curl / URL-for-Postman / `.http` / HTTPie | Other tooling or a quick paste |
| `QA-description` | Paste-ready PR markdown | Short PR text — not scenario checklists |

---

## Workflow

Full details in `SKILL.md` (install path: `~/.cursor/skills/qa-testing/SKILL.md`). Summary:

### 1. Ticket key
`git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD` → extract `TOPS-1234`. If none, ask.

### 2. Diff
```bash
BASE=$(git merge-base origin/master HEAD 2>/dev/null || git merge-base origin/main HEAD)
git diff "$BASE"...HEAD --stat && git diff "$BASE"...HEAD
```

### 3. Read source
Before writing any URL/body/field — read the model and route files from the diff. Match field names verbatim.

#### Detect service type
- **`service-organization`** → TOPS (Scala/Play, direct).
- **`organization-management`** → BFF (Go/chi, aperture `Jwt-Identity` + `X-As-Member-Id`).

#### Discover real URL
Find router prefix, port (from config, not assumed `8080`), auth prefix, error shape, status code mapping, auth headers. Full path in every artifact.

### 4. Scenarios
Derive strictly from the diff. Cover: happy path, DL gating (OFF + ON), negative validation, DB persistence, delete. Edge cases not in diff → add as `(optional)`. DL present → Phase 1 / Phase 2 split.

**Tag each scenario with priority:**
- **Critical** — data loss, security, breaking contract change.
- **High** — core business logic of the change.
- **Medium** — edge cases explicitly in the diff.
- **Low** — optional/exploratory cases.

`QA-guide` includes Critical + High only. All other modes show all four with the label visible per scenario.

---

## Mode outputs

### `QA-scenarios` (chat)
Pre-requisites block + numbered list. Each item: 5–6 word label, URL, body (if any), one-line expected.

### `QA-notes` (.md)
Destination: `docs/` → `.idea/tickets/` → ask. File: `<TICKET>-QA-notes.md`.
One sentence "why" per scenario + DB/side-effect verification. No padding.

### `QA-guide` (.md)
Destination: same picker. File: `<TICKET>-QA-guide.md`.
5–7 bullets max. Format: **label** — `METHOD path` — `status` + key signal — `_Postman item N._`
No body, no URL host. Skip: 400 on bad type, 401 missing auth, generic 404 (unit tests cover those).

### `QA-postman` (.postman_collection.json)

**For BFF (`organization-management`):** Ask auth strategy first (Manual JWT / Auto-mint). Explain:
> `basicAuth` = `base64(email:password)`. Generate: `printf '%s' 'you@hootsuite.com:pass' | base64`. Paste as Current Value.

Ask default host (localhost / staginghost / devhost). All items use the same host — never mix.

Validate before reporting ready (run `tools/validate-postman.py <path>`). Full validation script + item structure in `SKILL.md`.

**Tests that don't belong:** "Missing X-As-Member-Id → 401" (act-as, not auth), "Wrong basic auth → 401" (tests aperture, not the service). Empty-body 401 → assert status only, no `json().code`.

### `QA-requests`
Ask format:
- **A) curl** — bash one-liners
- **B) URL + body** — paste into Postman manually (no collection file)
- **C) .http** — JetBrains / VS Code REST Client
- **D) HTTPie**
- **E) Other** — paste a sample and I'll mirror it

### `QA-description` (chat, English always)
Ticket + what changed (no changelog, version bumps, codegen churn) + Behavior before/after if user-visible + Risks if concrete. Target ~10–20 lines. No scenario lists.

---

## Chat output

Minimal noise. After mode is selected and artifacts are ready, use this shape (adapt fields to the mode):

```markdown
## [Artifact type] ready

**File**: `[path]` _(omit for chat-only modes)_

**Variables to fill** (Current Value): _(omit if none)_
- `[var1]` — [what it is]

**Auth strategy**: [Manual JWT | Auto-mint] _(QA-postman only)_
**DL flag**: [name + expected state, or "none"]

[N] scenarios: [P critical / Q high / R medium / S low].
```

No preamble, no workflow recap.
